properties.headline: Hydrologic Outlook issued January 27 at 9:57AM EST by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI
properties.description:
Minor flooding possible along the Saginaw River today as high water levels
on Saginaw Bay back water into the river. However, with the river expected
to remain below 18 feet and with no rainfall expected over the upcoming work week,
no flood warning will be issued.

FLOOD POTENTIAL TIME POTENTIAL MAGNITUDE
